# Automated testing (Playwright) conventions

For the contributor working on automated testing, largely independent of the
backend/frontend implementation tracks.

- Point test config at the Prism mock server
  (`npx @stoplight/prism-cli mock api/openapi.yaml`) by default, not the real
  backend — this is what lets testing proceed in parallel with backend/frontend
  work instead of blocking on it. Real-backend runs are a separate CI/local
  config, not the default.
- Contract conformance tests (asserting real backend responses match
  `api/openapi.yaml` schemas) are a distinct test suite from UI e2e tests —
  don't mix them into the same spec files.
- The full end-to-end happy path (build a graph → run it → see the result) is
  intentionally gated: the CI workflow's `e2e` job stays commented out until
  the underlying stack (graph translator, run endpoint, canvas save/run) is
  far enough along to support it. Write the test against the mock in the
  meantime so it's ready to enable, but don't fight to make it pass against a
  backend that isn't there yet.
- Use `data-testid` attributes for React Flow canvas interactions rather than
  relying on generated class names or DOM structure, which will shift as the
  canvas UI evolves.
- Each test should be runnable in isolation — no test that depends on state
  left behind by a previous test in the same file.
